<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-05T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="553" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3273: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)<note n="4" xml:id="d553fn4">The
                                same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, on the same date to
                                the Ambassador in Peru as telegram No. 19.</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-05T11:00:00-05:00">March 5, 1929—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>20. Your 27, March 3, noon. I expect to remain as Secretary of State
                            until about March 25 at which time my successor, Mr. Henry L. Stimson,
                            will arrive. I wish to do everything in my power during this time to
                            further a complete settlement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>